    "We focus on two of Karp's 21 NP-complete problems: Max-cut and 3-SAT 3, [38] [39] [40].",
    "Mapping these problems into an Ising Hamiltonian equation can be achieved by setting the appropriate coupling coefficients in the energy function 39, 41:",
    "Where J ij is a coupling coefficient between units i and j, which can be positive or negative and is usually achieved in an ONN using resistors 10 or capacitors 26, respectively.",
    "s i is the spin (up ↑ or down ↓) of unit i, which can be mapped in a binarized network of oscillators by the phase (0 or π).",
    "And h i is an external bias, representing the interaction of unit i with an external unit with fixed spin value."
